HIV/AIDS: Sabbin cututtuka sun karu da kashi 14 cikin 100 a China
Kasar Sin ta sanar da cewa yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da cutar kanjamau ya karu da kashi 14 cikin dari.
Jami'an kiwon lafiya sun ce sama da mutane 8,20,000 ne ke dauke da cutar a kasar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai, an sami sabbin mutane kusan 40,000.
Yawancin sababbin masu kamuwa da cutar sun kamu ne ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ke nuna canji a baya.
A al'adance, cutar HIV tana yaduwa cikin sauri a wasu sassan kasar Sin ta hanyar bayar da jini mai guba.
Amma a wannan hanyar, adadin masu kamuwa da cutar HIV ya ragu sosai, kuma ya kusan zuwa sifili, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Duk da haka, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS a kasar Sin ya karu da dubu ɗari a kowace shekara.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce ga al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
A cikin shekarar 1997, ba a sanya yin luwadi a matsayin laifi a kasar Sin ba, amma nuna bambanci ga mutanen LGBT ya karu a ko'ina.
Binciken ya nuna cewa kimanin kashi 70-90% na mazajen da suke yin jima'i da maza suna yin aure da mata saboda ra'ayoyin gargajiya na kasar.
Rashin kariya a cikin irin wannan alaƙar ne ke haifar da yawancin cututtuka.
Tun 2003, a matsayin wani ɓangare na ƙoƙarin magance matsalar, gwamnatin Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da magungunan cutar HIV a duniya.
